# IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP

## Phase 1: Core Foundation (Months 1-3)
**Focus: Basic practice management and clinical documentation**

### Sprint 1-2: Infrastructure
- Set up iOS project architecture
- Implement secure data storage with encryption
- Build user authentication system
- Create basic navigation structure

### Sprint 3-4: Clinical Documentation
- Implement SOAP notes with voice input
- Build basic intake forms
- Create client profile management
- Add session documentation

### Sprint 5-6: Scheduling Core
- Build appointment calendar
- Implement booking management
- Add basic availability settings
- Create appointment reminders

## Phase 2: Financial Management (Months 4-6)
**Focus: Complete bookkeeping and payment processing**

### Sprint 7-8: Payment Processing
- Integrate payment gateway
- Build invoice generation
- Implement payment tracking
- Add basic reporting

### Sprint 9-10: Bookkeeping System
- Create chart of accounts
- Build expense tracking
- Implement receipt scanning
- Add P&L reporting

### Sprint 11-12: Tax Management
- Build mileage tracking
- Create tax report generation
- Implement 1099 preparation
- Add quarterly estimates

## Phase 3: Insurance & Compliance (Months 7-9)
**Focus: Insurance billing and HIPAA compliance**

### Sprint 13-14: Insurance Billing
- Build claim generation
- Implement eligibility checking
- Create ERA processing
- Add denial management

### Sprint 15-16: Compliance Tools
- Implement HIPAA safeguards
- Build audit logging
- Create consent management
- Add security controls

### Sprint 17-18: License Management
- Build license tracking
- Create CE credit management
- Implement renewal reminders
- Add compliance dashboard

## Phase 4: Business Operations (Months 10-12)
**Focus: Marketing, analytics, and growth tools**

### Sprint 19-20: Marketing Automation
- Build email campaigns
- Create loyalty programs
- Implement review management
- Add referral tracking

### Sprint 21-22: Analytics Platform
- Build custom reporting
- Create dashboards
- Implement KPI tracking
- Add forecasting tools

### Sprint 23-24: Advanced Features
- Implement team management
- Build inventory tracking
- Create mobile therapist tools
- Add specialty features

## Phase 5: Optimization & Scaling (Months 13-15)
**Focus: Performance, integrations, and advanced features**

### Sprint 25-26: Integrations
- Build API connections
- Implement third-party sync
- Create data import/export
- Add webhook support

### Sprint 27-28: Performance
- Optimize database queries
- Implement caching strategies
- Build offline capabilities
- Add background sync

### Sprint 29-30: Polish
- Enhance UI/UX
- Add advanced customization
- Implement A/B testing
- Create onboarding flows

## Phase 6: Launch & Iteration (Months 16-18)
**Focus: Beta testing, launch, and continuous improvement**

### Sprint 31-32: Beta Program
- Recruit 100 beta testers
- Implement feedback system
- Fix critical issues
- Add requested features

### Sprint 33-34: Launch Preparation
- Create marketing materials
- Build support documentation
- Implement monitoring
- Add analytics tracking

### Sprint 35-36: Post-Launch
- Monitor performance
- Address user feedback
- Implement improvements
- Plan next features

